	<h1>Do the best work of your life</h1>
	<h2 style="color: #7d8d99; font-weight: 300; margin: 0;">Find clients and freelancers you love working with</h2>

	<p>Folyo is a platform that helps great companies find great freelancers (we were founded in 2011). We worked hard on the newest version of Folyo and we think you’re going to love it. Here’s what we believe.</p>

	<hr>

	<div class="manifesto" id="together">
		<h2>Clients and freelancers are in this together</h2>
	
		<p>They’re natural allies. They want the same thing: to do the  best work of their life. But most sites treat them like enemies. The start of a project isn’t the start of a war. This isn’t a fierce negotiation with a sworn enemy. There’s no need for a budget shakedown, project scope wrestling match, or any of the half a dozen other situations we’ve built up in our minds. The truth is both sides want the same thing: a quick, successful and profitable project. There’s more common ground than you think.</p>
	</div>

	<hr>
	
	<div class="manifesto" id="description">
		<h2>Project outcomes trump skills</h2>
	
		<p>Leave out the skill checkmarks and bullet-lists. They don’t matter. What you can do because of your skill is what matters. Focusing on the outcome of the specific project at hand will give you the best results. Projects aren’t about skills they’re about outcomes.</p>
		
		<!--
		<p><strong>Here are some articles we think you'll love:</strong></p>
